Choosing initial conditions in the 6D model

The following equations link the initial conditions of the 3d model to those of the 6d model: \(\omega_0 = \frac{w_0}{p_0 a_0}\), \(\lambda_0 = \frac{K}{\nu N_0 a_0}\), \(d_0 = \frac{\nu D_0}{p_0 K_0}\)

We have \(\nu=3\) and lets assume that \(p_0 = 1\) and \(N_0=1\).

Then we have \(\omega_0 = \frac{w_0}{a_0}\), \(\lambda_0 = \frac{K}{3 a_0}\), \(d_0 = \frac{3 D_0}{K_0}\).

Starting with the good intial conditions \((\lambda_0, \omega_0, d_0) = (0.9,0.9,0.3)\), we have \(10D = K = 2.7 a\) and \(w = 0.9 a\). So we can vary \(a\) and see if the results in the 6D model are the same.

a_seq <- seq(1,100,1)
K_seq <- 2.7 * a_seq
D_seq <- 0.27 * a_seq
w_seq <- 0.9 * a_seq

for (i in 1:100){
  IC_6d <- c(
  K  =  K_seq[i],
  w   =  w_seq[i],
  p   =  1,
  debt = D_seq[i],
  a = a_seq[i],
  pop = 1)
  
  Sim <- simulation_6d(time          = Time,
                     init_state       = IC_6d,
                     parms            = Parms,
                     method           = 'lsoda')

  cat('end result: lambda =', tail(Sim$lambda,1), 'omega =',
      tail(Sim$omega,1), 'debt share =', tail(Sim$debt_share,1),'\n')
}

We see that the end result varies a bit for choices of small \(a\), but as \(a\) increases the final results become similar. If you look at each plot, you see that with lower values of \(a\) there is some oscillation, but it flattens out quickly, then all the remaining plots looks the same.

Here are some plots. The code has been changed so that the output of the 3D model with the identical initial conditions and parameters is also plotted as a dashed line.

\(a=1\)

### Set initial conditions 
IC_6d <- c(
  K  =  2.7,
  w   =  0.9,
  p   =  1,
  debt = 0.27,
  a = 1,
  pop = 1
)

omega      <- IC_6d[['w']]/ (IC_6d[['p']] * IC_6d[['a']])
lambda     <- IC_6d[['K']]/ (IC_6d[['pop']] * IC_6d[['a']] * Parms[['nu']])
debt_share <- (IC_6d[['debt']] * Parms[['nu']]) / (IC_6d[['p']] * IC_6d[['K']])

IC_3d <- c(
  lambda  =  lambda, 
  omega   =  omega,
  debt    =  debt_share
)
#=================================================================================
# Set up simulation
Time <- c(
  start         =     2020, 
  end           =     2100,
  step          =     0.05
)

Options <- list(
  transform_vars  = FALSE  # T / F
)

# run both 
Sim_3d <- simulation_3d(time = Time,
                  init_state = IC_3d,
                  parms      = Parms,
                  options    = Options,
                  method     = 'lsoda')

Sim_6d <- simulation_6d(time          = Time,
                     init_state       = IC_6d,
                     parms            = Parms,
                     method           = 'lsoda')
